In this part of the project we are basically creating a randomized Pokémon-style terrain generator using C. Over here, we  basically create a 21×80 map with impassable borders, randomly placed exits on all four sides, and curved roads that connect exits to ensure full connectivity.Then, we also  multiple terrain regions such as tall grass, mountains, and water which are generated using random-walk algorithms to produce a scattered and a  natural-looking map. Each execution of the program generates a random terrain layout while respecting the structural constraints defined in the assignment.